<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1185> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1185" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap. (names entire); Gell. 10.6.4; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; Degrassi 42f., 116, 436f. Both probably campaigned in Sicily (Zon. 8.16)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1121> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1121" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap. (names entire); Act. Tr., on Messala; Polyb. 1.16.1; Eutrop. 2.19; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; Zon. 8.9; see Degrassi, 40f., 115, 432f. Valerius captured many Sicilian towns, received the submission of Syracuse, and celebrated a triumph over the Carthaginians and King Hiero (Polyb. 1.16-17; Zon. 8.9; cf. Naevius, fr. 32, with praenomen M.; Liv. Per. 16; Diod. 23.4; Flor. 1.18.6;{204} Eutrop. 2.19; Oros. 4.7.2; and on the triumph, Piso fr. 29 Peter; Varro, in Plin. NH 7.214, with praenomen M.; Cic. Fam. 14.2.2; Vat. 21, and Schol. Bob. ad loc.; Act. Tr., Degrassi, 74f., 547f.; Plin. NH 35.22; Censorin. 23.7; Eutrop. 2.19). Otacilius also campaigned in Sicily (Polyb. 1.16-17; Frontin. Str. 4.1.19; Eutrop. 2.19; Zon. 8.9). On Valerius, see Münzer, Gent. Val. 50, no. 51; on Otacilius, Lübker no. 1." .
